DangDam.bsp Read Me
Map by Arrogant Orange(in game name: MIR\/EN-131)
To use with:Counter-Strike: SOURCE
Made with: SOURCE SDK
Version: 1.NL / status: Functional

=================================================

Contents of folder:
1x DangDam.bsp map file
1x DangDam.nav BOT Navagation file
1x DangDam.txt Intro screen text file 
3x Screen Shots
1x DangDam_Readme.txt file

=================================================

Map Story: 

OK, so the Terrorists have entered into the dock threw the sewers with the objective of obliterating the tanker that is being serviced in the dry dock. Due to the main maintenance elevator being down for repair the T's have chosen to attack while the dock workers are on leave. The Docks Security team was having lunch in the rec room near the wood shop when the commotion that took place when the T-Forces made breech in the Service Warehouse alerted them.



Map description:

DangDam.bsp was just a map I started for fun. Like most of my maps DangDam started out as a fascination with another map I was ether playing or some movie I was watching(007 LOL.) The objective, in DangDam, is the classic "de_" mission, which is to ether place the bomb in the bomb site(T-Forces)or to Defuse the active bomb(CT-Forces). The one and only bomb site is located on top of the tanker ship. Aside from the OG de style the map dose offer an interesting Fight-Yard aspect since the huge ship is in the way and the dock is drained so there is a huge valley in between the two spawn points.

Side Note(s):

+I had previously posted DangDam.bsp a while back but I forgot that I had used a few models and textures from DOD:S and that I hadn't included any of said files with the up-loaded .zip. Also I got a few comments one from a fellow banananner(Can't  remember who since I deleted the file soon afterwards)who said that he detested the idea of having two wildly different Bomb  Sites. He also noted that having a Bomb-Site atop the dam just wasn't all that great(or at least i think he/she did.) So, I  made those few fixes and then added a few more additions. Manly building and atmosphere changes. I also had to remove the  lighting, for this build version: 1.NL(NL=No Lights,)as it was eating up my PC's resource consumption during the compiling.

+The crossing tunnel(the big cylinder in the dock ravine)can be penetrated by heavy fire. So shoot it up if you want. 




=================================================

Bugs/ Known Issues:

+The map is missing a few different bits of detail here and there.

+Some of the terrain MIGHT not be lined up correctly.

+The BOT's don't really move until you fire at them or if they see you. The T-Forces will advance but will all fall into the  dock ravine. They won't die but they will just run back and forth down in there. And they've never used the crossing  tunnel...EVER! Most likely I'll have to add a ladder to the CT_forces side of the dock too.

+Um...oh and the lighting sucks, as always X)

+The main part of the map works nicely and it fits the theme but the dam and the inside part is just a waste of space at the  moment. 

+Only the red barrels and the gas can on the ladder lift will take hit-points away. The air or propane tanks(the red long slender tanks)don't damage the players at all.  

=================================================

CT Support Facility is a medium sized map set for 20 players. Intel has provided info that Terrorists have hidden in shipping containers and gained access to the base. CT's start in Headquarters and the Terrorists start in the container area. Bomb sites are Headquarters and Personal barracks.

Should run good, not a whole lot of imported or authored models, nav file is edited and included in bsp. Compiled for HDR - BLOOM ONLY!

Been awhile since I have done anything in source so any and all comments are welcomed.

ATTN:

I had a few problems with HDR so please set to bloom or map will appear silver.

-BACKGROUND-
A group of Counter-Terrorists were sent out to a junkyard in the middle east that had been reporting suspicious behavior for the past couple weeks. Having trouble navigating the terrain, their APCs crashed just outside the scrapyard. Upon arrival, they find it deserted. As the CTs are about to call for a chopper, gunshots are heard from over the ridge. The CTs take shelter in the nearby shed and prepare to meet the incoming Terrorist force head on.

-MAP INFORMATION-
The Terrorist spawn is behind three containers outside the junkyard. There are lights that sort of map out a path to the junkyard entrance. Near the crashed APCs (mentioned above) there are M4a1s and USPs. The CTs will spawn in one of the two buildings inside the scrapyard (there are FAMASes and Five-Sevens on the tables). The two bombsites are the center of the junked cars, and the crane outside the junk area. Many props provide cover, and the bots WILL use it.

Cette map est une defuse map, l'action se passe près d'un complexe de raffinerie, en Europe de l'Est ou Centrale
Deux objectifs sont disponibles, un tuyau de jonction ou une salle de test et controle du pétrole.
Un passage souterrain permet de relier les deux objectifs en plus de deux passages ouverts.
La map a été concu pour une action rapide mais de nombreux endroits permettent les embuscades, le sniping, les coudes des passages, les salles, les terrains et autres modles, recoins de la map sont autant de possibilitées.
Des armes (rifles) sont disponibles chez les terroristes dans les deux vehicules situés au depart.
La map fonctionne bien avec de 15 à 22 joueurs environ, plus provoque le ralentissement des FPS et donc la map rame a 32 joueurs; mais cela peut aussi dépendre de votre configuration
Les points de navigations pour les bots sont fournis et marchent très bien.

The doors to heaven and hell have been opened, and some extremist retards
have entered into the realm of the suffering to establish a base of operations.

throne. They know that the masonry and metallurgy required to rebuild the seat
of God could take a few days, maybe even weeks, to repair! God, being omnipresent,
obviously knows of this attack, and has hired some elite counter-terrorist units
from the human world to prevent this. And while they're at it, they can do
their best to save some souls from the underworld, if possible.

CTs- Kill those terrorists. if possible, attempt to save some souls from hell,
they could use some relief.

Terrorists- Blow up the throne of God, and escape!

Cobble 3k by -FuzzyFish-:

The year is 2085, it has been almost a century since a long forgotten attack was launched by the terrorist organization known as the Special Terrorism Recon Infiltration Killing Echelon. Or rather STRIKE for short, attempted to attack a small town little known town in the year 2001.

Fortunately, the governments of the world had united in the cause and formed a team of counter-terrorists known very simply as Counter-STRIKE (Counter Special Terrorism Recon Infiltration Killing Echelon). This group of minimally trained individuals working loosely as a team, successfully defended this locale. Among many other specifically chosen high value targets, such as:

- Poor run down slums in the desert
- Box canyons
- Enclosed industrial complexes
- Docks located oddly in isolated waters
- Four random ice spires in the artic tundra
- Large fragile glass buildings
- Zombie reservations

After the DustÃƒï¿½Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂ¯Ã‚Â¿Ã‚Â½Ãƒï¿½Ã‚Â¢ settled, Counter-STRIKE emerged the winner. But not at a cost any less than millions of lives, and trillions of dollars. Leaving governments around the world not only pennyless, but also low on defense forces. STRIKE was never heard from again, and the remains of Counter-STRIKE were disbanded.

It was at this decisive moment that large coorperations moved in taking over every inch of towns, and cities that they could. And with great success, many people welcomed a change from years of bloody battles. And welcomed the endless onslaght of fast-food, coffee, and electronics. Time moved on, everything moved on, it was an endless movement. 

Yet no matter how much one moves on. Somethings never change, it was at this time STRIKE with the aid of an acquired vehicle allowing time travel struck back. At a time when the world knew nothing but peace, chubby people, and laziness. They were ready for a change, and once again the people had a cause to rally behind, it was time once more for Counter-STRIKE.


HINT: Rumor has it the time-travelling car STRIKE used can be found parked carelessly around town. Perhaps it could be used to fight back against them.



Credits:
- -FuzzyFish- - Map, Textures, Sound Editing, Testing, etc.
- David Johnston - Creator of de_cbble, and other CS maps. For which this layout is based.
- Crystal Castles - Edited sound loop for a secret.
- Hide - Edited sound loop. A small if not underwhelming tribute to Hondo's mapping excellence/insanity.

Notes:
- Mapping, not a bad way to spend a military deployment in the desert. 
- Said car can be driven around with a friend. Shoot for the windows, enjoy.
